1487
01:20:57,040 --> 01:21:00,240
and is based upon suggestions found in the 1960 guide

1488
01:21:00,240 --> 01:21:04,160
to the standard progressive matrices written by John C. Raven,

1489
01:21:04,160 --> 01:21:08,640
AKA the guy what invented the Raven's Progressive Matrices test.

1490
01:21:08,640 --> 01:21:10,880
After reporting the findings of Pons,

1491
01:21:10,880 --> 01:21:13,360
Crawford Knott takes things one step further

1492
01:21:13,360 --> 01:21:17,200
and tests a selection of pupils from a long-established high school

1493
01:21:17,200 --> 01:21:22,080
situated in the black residential area of Soweto near Johannesburg,

1494
01:21:22,080 --> 01:21:24,720
a school that is described as having high standards

1495
01:21:24,720 --> 01:21:27,680
and whose students would be used to being tested.

1496
01:21:27,680 --> 01:21:30,640
Crawford Knott tested two samples of these schoolchildren

1497
01:21:30,640 --> 01:21:33,680
using the same presentation method as described by Pons,

1498
01:21:33,680 --> 01:21:36,400
