and all the air quotes science is just window dressing for that agenda.

2231
02:02:39,280 --> 02:02:41,520
And that's what we're going to talk about next.

2232
02:02:41,520 --> 02:02:44,560
So then, the politics of the bell curve.

2233
02:02:44,640 --> 02:02:49,920
And I'd like to first talk a bit more about why the bell curve was so controversial.

2234
02:02:49,920 --> 02:02:55,520
And there's one main reason comprised of two, uh, sub reasons.

2235
02:02:56,160 --> 02:02:59,520
The first is that Herrnstein and Murray spend a large part of their book

2236
02:02:59,520 --> 02:03:04,080
asserting differences in intelligence between designated racial groups.

2237
02:03:04,080 --> 02:03:06,800
And we have to wonder why they even did this,

2238
02:03:06,800 --> 02:03:09,840
because it isn't important at all for their overall point.

2239
02:03:10,480 --> 02:03:14,080
Their main argument is that IQ is the most important factor

2240
02:03:14,080 --> 02:03:16,400
determining success or failure in life,

2241
02:03:16,400 --> 02:03:20,080
and they seemingly don't need the racial element at all to make this point.

2242
02:03:20,720 --> 02:03:21,920
Or do they?

2243
02:03:22,560 --> 02:03:26,480
In a section titled How Ethnic Differences Fit Into the Story,

2244
02:03:26,480 --> 02:03:27,920
they write the following.

2245
02:03:27,920 --> 02:03:31,920
In part one, we described the formation of a cognitive elite.

2246
02:03:31,920 --> 02:03:35,040
Given the cognitive differences among ethnic and racial groups,

2247
02:03:35,040 --> 02:03:38,560
the cognitive elite cannot represent all groups equally,

2248
02:03:38,560 --> 02:03:41,920
a statement with implications that we will develop in part four.

2249
02:03:42,640 --> 02:03:47,040
Part four being the section of the book comprised of their policy proposals,

2250
02:03:47,040 --> 02:03:51,040
and it is these policy proposals that are the second part of the reason

2251
02:03:51,040 --> 02:03:54,080
for the bell curve being such a controversial book.

2252
02:03:54,080 --> 02:03:58,000
More than either of these things individually being controversial,

2253
02:03:58,000 --> 02:04:01,920
it's how they interact that really produces the controversy.

2254
02:04:01,920 --> 02:04:06,000
You see, for all Herrnstein and Murray's posturing about how brave they're being,

2255
02:04:06,000 --> 02:04:08,640
speaking out and breaking taboos and all that,

2256
02:04:08,640 --> 02:04:12,240
it is not actually controversial in the scientific community

2257
02:04:12,240 --> 02:04:15,920
to simply acknowledge group differences in IQ.

2258
02:04:15,920 --> 02:04:18,000
Let's imagine that instead of the bell curve,

2259
02:04:18,000 --> 02:04:22,080
Herrnstein and Murray had simply published a list of IQ test results

2260
02:04:22,080 --> 02:04:24,960
showing differences in IQ in different countries.

2261
02:04:25,600 --> 02:04:27,280
Nobody would have cared.

2262
02:04:27,280 --> 02:04:29,600
Researchers from across the political spectrum

2263
02:04:29,600 --> 02:04:32,560
work with intelligence test data all the time.

2264
02:04:32,560 --> 02:04:34,640
Some environment-minded researchers,

2265
02:04:34,640 --> 02:04:37,840
because they acknowledge that the group differences exist,

2266
02:04:37,840 --> 02:04:40,720
but they want to prove that environmental factors

2267
02:04:40,720 --> 02:04:42,560
are the key to understanding them.

2268
02:04:42,560 --> 02:04:46,720
Nor is it controversial to assert that differences in cognitive ability

2269
02:04:46,720 --> 02:04:49,680
in general are partially due to genetics.

2270
02:04:49,680 --> 02:04:55,040
There are a whole host of genetic conditions that can affect someone's cognitive ability.

2271
02:04:55,040 --> 02:04:58,160
Right-wingers who characterize lefties as die-hard,

2272
02:04:58,160 --> 02:05:01,520
100% environmentalists miss the point here,

2273
02:05:01,520 --> 02:05:04,400
as we'd actually be hasty to point out the ableism

2274
02:05:04,400 --> 02:05:07,360
in denying the effects of those genetic conditions.

2275
02:05:07,840 --> 02:05:11,920
So it's not simply that Herrnstein and Murray are breaking the supposed taboo

2276
02:05:11,920 --> 02:05:15,840
of discussing IQ differences that sparked the backlash.

2277
02:05:15,840 --> 02:05:21,200
It's that they explicitly link those differences to a set of policy proposals.

2278
02:05:21,200 --> 02:05:26,400
This is why the bell curve is controversial, because of its political ideas.

2279
02:05:26,400 --> 02:05:27,840
So let's talk about those.

2280
02:05:28,560 --> 02:05:30,880
First off, the enormous glaring problem

2281
02:05:30,880 --> 02:05:34,560
with the vast majority of Herrnstein and Murray's policy proposals

2282
02:05:34,560 --> 02:05:37,680
is that they absolutely do not logically follow

2283
02:05:37,680 --> 02:05:40,640
from any of their previous claims in the bell curve.

2284
02:05:40,640 --> 02:05:45,200
And if it sounds like I'm exaggerating there, trust me, I am not.

2285
02:05:45,200 --> 02:05:48,640
Take, for instance, their account of programs like Head Start

2286
02:05:48,640 --> 02:05:51,280
that are designed to help disadvantaged kids.

2287
02:05:51,840 --> 02:05:54,480
Herrnstein and Murray acknowledge that these programs

2288
02:05:54,480 --> 02:05:56,960
can have temporary positive effects,

2289
02:05:56,960 --> 02:06:00,480
but they argue that these positive effects fade over time

2290
02:06:00,480 --> 02:06:05,280
and become statistically insignificant by the time those children leave school.

2291
02:06:05,280 --> 02:06:07,600
This is taken by Herrnstein and Murray as proof

2292
02:06:07,600 --> 02:06:11,200
that there is ultimately nothing to be done to help these kids.

2293
02:06:11,200 --> 02:06:14,800
Any temporary positive effects will simply fade away

2294
02:06:14,800 --> 02:06:17,200
due to their inferior genetics.

2295
02:06:17,200 --> 02:06:19,440
So we should stop wasting money on them

2296
02:06:19,440 --> 02:06:22,800
and instead give it to the naturally gifted children.

2297
02:06:22,800 --> 02:06:24,800
This does not follow, however.

2298
02:06:24,800 --> 02:06:27,760
There is an alternative interpretation of this situation,

2299
02:06:27,760 --> 02:06:29,360
which is perfectly consistent

2300
02:06:29,360 --> 02:06:33,440
with a majority environmental understanding of childhood development.

2301
02:06:34,160 --> 02:06:37,120
We can argue that these programs produce a positive effect

2302
02:06:37,120 --> 02:06:40,320
because they are changing the children's environment.

2303
02:06:40,320 --> 02:06:43,520
Any diminished effects after the programs stop

2304
02:06:43,520 --> 02:06:46,080
are because the programs stopped,

2305
02:06:46,080 --> 02:06:49,360
thus changing the environment back to the norm.

2306
02:06:49,360 --> 02:06:51,520
So instead of abandoning these programs,

2307
02:06:51,520 --> 02:06:53,040
we should instead take them as proof

2308
02:06:53,040 --> 02:06:56,880
that environmental changes can produce positive effects

2309
02:06:56,880 --> 02:07:00,480
and then expand them, increase their funding,

2310
02:07:00,480 --> 02:07:04,080
have equivalent programs for every stage of school life.

2311
02:07:04,080 --> 02:07:08,240
Any later diminished effects are proof that we aren't trying hard enough,

2312
02:07:08,240 --> 02:07:11,280
not that what we're trying to do is impossible.

2313
02:07:11,280 --> 02:07:13,920
Nearly every policy proposal in the bell curve

2314
02:07:13,920 --> 02:07:17,200
has this sort of alternative explanation.

2315
02:07:17,200 --> 02:07:21,760
One of their proposals for dissuading low IQ mothers from having children

2316
02:07:21,760 --> 02:07:25,040
is to stop the welfare programs that support them.

2317
02:07:25,040 --> 02:07:28,720
But as we know, richer people tend to have fewer children,

2318
02:07:28,720 --> 02:07:33,120
and birth rates are lower in countries with comprehensive welfare programs.

2319
02:07:33,760 --> 02:07:37,680
Making these women poorer will not make them have fewer children.

2320
02:07:37,680 --> 02:07:40,160
And besides, Hernstein and Murray are arguing

2321
02:07:40,160 --> 02:07:43,120
that these women are resolutely unintelligent.

2322
02:07:43,120 --> 02:07:44,320
So if that were true,

2323
02:07:44,320 --> 02:07:47,520
why would we be expecting them to be able to plan ahead

2324
02:07:47,520 --> 02:07:51,360
and reason logically that having fewer children is a good idea?

2325
02:07:51,360 --> 02:07:54,320
That they're not supposed to be able to plan well for the future

2326
02:07:54,320 --> 02:07:56,000
is kind of the whole point, right?

2327
02:07:56,560 --> 02:07:58,480
What Hernstein and Murray could have done here

2328
02:07:58,480 --> 02:08:03,120
is some very basic comparisons between the United States and other countries.

2329
02:08:03,120 --> 02:08:06,640
They scaremonger about the possible effects of welfare programs

2330
02:08:06,640 --> 02:08:09,760
which exist in Europe in abundance, for instance.

2331
02:08:09,760 --> 02:08:12,160
But since those European welfare programs

2332
02:08:12,160 --> 02:08:14,720
have not led to the sort of utter catastrophe

2333
02:08:14,720 --> 02:08:16,720
that Hernstein and Murray prophesize,

2334
02:08:16,720 --> 02:08:20,400
they instead choose to focus only on the United States.

2335
02:08:20,400 --> 02:08:22,880
Even if Hernstein and Murray had proven

2336
